  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 190°C/ 170°C (fan)/ gas 5 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced beef</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) <strong>half</strong> the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
