    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef is lightly browned, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to dish with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> grated mushroom </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Cook for 3 min further or until everything has slightly softened</p><p>Add the <strong>beef stock mix </strong>with<strong> </strong>450ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 1hr 15 min – this is your<strong> beef & mushroom ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
